%% AutomationOS System Call Sequence
%% Mermaid Sequence Diagram
%% Render with: mmdc -i seq_syscall.mmd -o ../seq_syscall.svg

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Userspace<br/>(Ring 3)
    participant Lib as libc
    participant CPU as CPU<br/>(syscall instruction)
    participant Entry as Syscall Entry<br/>(syscall.asm)
    participant Dispatch as Syscall Dispatcher<br/>(syscall.c)
    participant Handler as Syscall Handler<br/>(handlers.c)
    participant Kernel as Kernel Subsystem<br/>(sched/mem/drivers)

    Note over User,Kernel: Example: write(1, "Hello", 5)

    User->>Lib: write(1, "Hello", 5)
    activate Lib
    Note over Lib: Prepare syscall:<br/>rax=SYS_WRITE<br/>rdi=fd, rsi=buf, rdx=count

    Lib->>CPU: syscall instruction
    deactivate Lib
    activate CPU
    Note over CPU: Hardware transition:<br/>• CPL 3 → 0 (ring 3 → 0)<br/>• RIP → IA32_LSTAR MSR<br/>• Save user RIP to RCX<br/>• Save RFLAGS to R11<br/>• Load kernel RSP

    CPU->>Entry: Jump to syscall_entry
    deactivate CPU
    activate Entry
    Note over Entry: Save user context:<br/>• Push all registers<br/>• Save user stack<br/>• Switch to kernel stack<br/>• Clear direction flag

    Entry->>Dispatch: syscall_dispatch(rax, rdi, rsi, rdx, ...)
    deactivate Entry
    activate Dispatch

    Note over Dispatch: Validate syscall number:<br/>if (rax >= MAX_SYSCALLS)<br/>  return -ENOSYS

    Dispatch->>Dispatch: Lookup handler in table
    Note over Dispatch: syscall_table[rax]

    Dispatch->>Handler: sys_write(fd, buf, count)
    activate Handler

    Handler->>Handler: Validate arguments:<br/>• Check fd bounds<br/>• Validate user buffer<br/>• Check size limits

    alt Invalid arguments
        Handler-->>Dispatch: return -EINVAL
    else Valid arguments
        Handler->>Kernel: serial_write(buf, count)
        activate Kernel
        Note over Kernel: Write to serial port<br/>(or TTY buffer)
        Kernel-->>Handler: return bytes_written
        deactivate Kernel
        Handler-->>Dispatch: return bytes_written
    end
    deactivate Handler

    Dispatch->>Dispatch: Update audit log
    Note over Dispatch: Log syscall:<br/>• PID, syscall number<br/>• Arguments, return value<br/>• Timestamp

    Dispatch-->>Entry: return result in rax
    deactivate Dispatch
    activate Entry

    Note over Entry: Restore user context:<br/>• Pop registers<br/>• Restore user stack

    Entry->>CPU: sysretq instruction
    deactivate Entry
    activate CPU
    Note over CPU: Hardware transition:<br/>• CPL 0 → 3 (ring 0 → 3)<br/>• RIP ← RCX (user RIP)<br/>• RFLAGS ← R11<br/>• Load user RSP

    CPU-->>Lib: Return to userspace
    deactivate CPU
    activate Lib
    Lib-->>User: return bytes_written
    deactivate Lib

    Note over User,Kernel: Total latency: ~500-1000 cycles<br/>(~0.2-0.5 μs on 2 GHz CPU)
